h blocked-window information to support much of the framework:\n  - hour stamp\n  - bias score\n  - PM price state (`Y... N...`)\n  - repeated adjacent-window observations\n- That means current logs can already support:\n  - signal density\n  - directional skew\n  - price-state cleanliness\n  - persistence / adjacent-window tracking\n- Wrote collection artifact: `/home/ubuntu/clawd/patches/v10r-low-instrumentation-03h-shadow-metric-collection.spec.md`\n\n**My thinking:**\nI\u2019m glad this doesn\u2019t need a heavy build. The right move is to squeeze value from the logs we already have before inventing a new instrumentation layer. That keeps the 03h research path lightweight and fast.\n\n**Decision:**\n- Start with offline extraction from existing logs.\n- Add only one small extra instrumentation line later if a concrete missing metric remains, for example a structured `03h` shadow-candidate line.\n\n**Next:** On the next P2 heartbeat, define the exact offline extraction fields and output table for a first-pass `03h` shadow dataset using current logs only.\n\n---\n## 2026-04-23 04:2",
